                <h1>Understanding Leukemia: Symptoms, Causes, and Treatments</h1>
                <p>Leukemia is a type of cancer that affects the blood and bone marrow, leading to the overproduction of abnormal white blood cells. It disrupts the body's ability to fight infections and can lead to severe health complications. Symptoms include fatigue, frequent infections, and easy bruising. Early diagnosis and treatment are crucial.</p>
